# creating deviation plot

net_rating_plot <- ggplot(net_rtg, aes(x = reorder(team, sum_rating), y = sum_rating)) +
  geom_bar(stat = "identity",
           fill = color,
           color = "gray30",
           show.legend = FALSE,
           width = 0.7) +
  geom_text(aes(label = round(sum_rating, 1),
                hjust = 0.5,
                vjust = ifelse(sum_rating < 0, 1.5, -1)),
                size = 3) +
  scale_x_discrete(
    name = NULL,
    labels = labels
  ) +
  geom_hline(yintercept = 0, color = 1, lwd = 1) +
  scale_y_continuous(limits = c(min(net_rtg$sum_rating) - 0.2,
                                max(net_rtg$sum_rating) + 0.2)) +
  labs(x = "Team",
       y = "Cumulative Net Rating",
       title = "Cumulative Net Rating for NBA Teams (2007-2021)") +
  theme_minimal() +
  theme(axis.text.y = element_blank(),  
        axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.x = element_blank(), 
        panel.grid.major.y = element_blank(),
        panel.grid.major.x = element_blank(),
        axis.text.x = ggtext::element_markdown(),
        plot.title = element_text(face = "bold")) 

# displaying net rating plot
net_rating_plot

# saving plot
ggsave("net_rating_plot.jpg", plot = net_rating_plot)

VORP Plot

# aggregating data to combine rows where player played for more than one team in a given year - ensure each player has one row per season for their career
player_data_agg <- player %>%
  group_by(nbapersonid, season) %>%
  summarize(
    player = first(player),
    draftyear = first(draftyear),
    draftpick = first(draftpick),
    games = sum(games),
    games_start = sum(games_start),
    points = sum(points),
    mins = sum(mins),
    fgm = sum(fgm),
    fga = sum(fga),
    fgm3 = sum(fgm3),
    fga3 = sum(fga3),
    fgm2 = sum(fgm2),
    fga2 = sum(fga2),
    ftm = sum(ftm),
    off_reb = sum(off_reb),
    def_reb = sum(def_reb),
    tot_reb = sum(tot_reb),
    ast = sum(ast),
    steals = sum(steals),
    blocks = sum(blocks),
    tov = sum(tov),
    tot_fouls = sum(tot_fouls),
    VORP = mean(VORP),
    PER = mean(PER)
  ) %>%
  ungroup()

# subset data to only include top 10 seasons by VORP
top_n_seasons <- player_data_agg %>%
  arrange(desc(VORP)) %>%
  slice_head(n = 10)

  mutate(player = case_when(
    player == "LeBron James" & row_number() == 1 ~ "Lebron James 1",
    player == "LeBron James" & row_number() == 2 ~ "LeBron James 2",
    player == "LeBron James" & row_number() == 3 ~ "LeBron James 3",
    player == "LeBron James" & row_number() == 5 ~ "LeBron James 4",
    player == "Chris Paul" & row_number() == 4 ~ "Chris Paul 1",
    player == "Chris Paul" & row_number() == 10 ~ "Chris Paul 2",
    TRUE ~ player
  ))

# ordering top seasons based on VORP so team colors can match

  "Lebron James 1", "LeBron James 2", "LeBron James 3", "Chris Paul 1", "Nikola Jokic",

))

All NBA Teams Stat Table

# merging aggregated player data and awards data
merged_player_data <- merge(player_data_agg, awards, by = c("season", "nbapersonid"), all = TRUE)

# filtering data to only include rows where players are selected for All NBA Teams
merged_player_data_all_nba <- merged_player_data %>% 
  filter(`All NBA First Team` == 1 |
           `All NBA Second Team` == 1 |
           `All NBA Third Team` == 1)

# creating per game stats columns
merged_player_data_all_nba <- 
  merged_player_data_all_nba %>% 
  mutate(ppg = points/games,
         rpg = tot_reb/games,
         apg = ast/games)

# calculating average points, rebounds, and assists for each All-NBA team
first_team_avg <- merged_player_data_all_nba %>%
  filter(`All NBA First Team` == 1) %>%
  summarise(
    Avg_Points = mean(ppg),
    Avg_Rebounds = mean(rpg),
    Avg_Assists = mean(apg)
  )

second_team_avg <- merged_player_data_all_nba %>%
  filter(`All NBA Second Team` == 1) %>%
  summarise(
    Avg_Points = mean(ppg),
    Avg_Rebounds = mean(rpg),
    Avg_Assists = mean(apg)
  )

third_team_avg <- merged_player_data_all_nba %>%
  filter(`All NBA Third Team` == 1) %>%
  summarise(
    Avg_Points = mean(ppg),
    Avg_Rebounds = mean(rpg),
    Avg_Assists = mean(apg)
  )

# combining the results into a single data.table
result <- rbind(round(first_team_avg, 2), round(second_team_avg, 2), 
                round(third_team_avg, 2))

# creating paged_table
rmarkdown::paged_table(result)
# saving table as a csv
write.csv(result, "~/Downloads/all_nba_data.csv", row.names=FALSE)

Rookie PER Density Plot

# subset data to only include rookie season rows
# creating draft status column based on draft pick number
# reordering draft status based on highest to lowest draft classification
player_rookies <- player_data_agg %>% 
  filter(draftyear == season) %>% 
  mutate(draft_status = case_when(
    draftpick <= 14 ~ "lottery",
    draftpick <= 30 ~ "first round",
    draftpick <= 60 ~ "second round",
    is.na(draftpick) ~ "undrafted"
  )) %>% 
  mutate(draft_status = fct_relevel(draft_status, "lottery", "first round", "second round", "undrafted"))

# creating PER plot
rookie_per_plot <- player_rookies %>% 
  ggplot(aes(x = PER, fill = draft_status)) +
  xlim(-10, 50) +
  geom_density(alpha = 0.5) +
  scale_fill_discrete(name = "Draft Status") +
  theme_minimal() +
  labs(x = "Player Efficiency Rating",
       y = NULL,
       title = "Distribution of Rookie Player Efficiency Ratings by Draft Status") +
  theme(plot.title = element_text(face = "bold"))

# displaying PER plot
rookie_per_plot

# saving PER plot
ggsave("rookie_per_plot.jpg", plot = rookie_per_plot)
